Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[France is in that difficult stage of truly sporadic anthrax and of persuading livestock owners to vaccinate their stock in areas perceived to be at risk. And it is the procrastinators that allow the disease to persist as their stock succumbs to infection. It takes much hard work by the regional veterinary staff to get the active attention and participation by their livestock owners. The spores are not immortal so the trick is to not replace the dying spores with fresh live ones from yet another outbreak. A total of 5 years without outbreaks is a good indicator that eradication is coming. Our thanks to Susan for the translation. - Mod.MHJ]
